18.20	National_Development_and_Reform_Commission	National Development and Reform Commission	The National Development and Reform Commission (NDRC; simplified Chinese: ; traditional Chinese: ; pinyin: Guójiā Fāzhǎn hé Gǎigé Wěiyuánhuì, or in short Chinese: ), formerly State Planning Commission and State Development Planning Commission, is a macroeconomic management agency under the Chinese State Council, which has broad administrative and planning control over the Chinese economy. Since 2008 the Commission has been headed by Zhang Ping.	
